From: post-bo-patch-prep
Subject: [PATCH 03/04] Exp C + R2: time_mgr phase re-skew + 220s cumulative cap

Per docs/audit/ARCH_CONTRARIAN_APR17.md §4 Experiment C and
docs/audit/LOSS_FORENSICS_APR17.md §4.R2.

Exp C — redirect the time budget from low-information openings into
the tactical mid-game:
  opening   (turns_left > 30):      0.6× → 0.3×
  mid       (10 < turns_left ≤ 30): 1.0× → 1.3×
  endgame   (turns_left ≤ 10):      use 2.5× (was 3.5× at ≤ 5 only)

R2 — defensive reduction of endgame multiplier from 3.5× to 2.5× (now
the endgame phase multiplier in Exp C) AND a hard cumulative ceiling
of 220 s total play time. The `cumulative_used >= 220` guard returns
a floor budget so search aborts and we ship the best-so-far / fallback
move, eliminating the Match-2-vs-alexBot "finished at 241 s" failure
mode.

Critical-belief composition preserved: when `turns_left <= 4` or
`max_mass >= 0.35`, the phase multiplier is lifted to the 1.6×
critical floor (via max). ENDGAME_TURNS_THRESHOLD widens 5 → 10 so
the endgame phase/ceiling line up.

Adds 2 tests per task brief: `test_multiplier_by_phase` and
`test_220s_cumulative_cap`.

